-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/IMG_2193_small.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Many fans of tabletop miniatures gaming feel as though the largest franchises in the space have, sadly, lost their edge. <em>Mordheim</em> co-designer Tuomas Pirinen counts himself among their number. \u201cIt\u2019s very homogenous,\u201d he told Polygon in a recent video interview. \u201cWhen I was a kid growing up, [there were] all these different artists with their own strong styles that you could immediately tell apart. I would like to bring that back.\u201d That is why he partnered with prolific concept artist Michael Franchina, an influential voice in the creation of the modern Dia", "id": 1408481, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/470132/trench-crusade-mike-franchina-tuomas-pirinen-kickstarter-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Trench Crusade unchains the grimmest, darkest sci-fi miniatures universe", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-29T10:05:49+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/black-ops-6-jackal-pdw-loadout-header.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As soon as you unlock the <strong>Jackal PDW </strong>in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.co